      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ENCRYPTIX (1) showed good early speed on debut and fought on well to run second over 1100m at Gosford in a solid rating contest. Has upside and can open his account from the good gate. HILLBILLY HIPPIE (7) wound up strongly on resumption with a slashing second from back in the field over 1100m at Armidale. Sure to derive great benefit from that run and doesn't have to improve much to win this. SUNVOLT (5) deep into the campaign and gets a much better setup for this. Snagged back from the wide gate and hit the line well to finish fourth over 800m at this track two weeks ago. Strong top-three chance. HE IS THE KISS (2) professional placegetter adept in all conditions. Chipped away late with a respectable second over 1200m at Gold Coast. The wide gate could prove the right place to be.",
